✔ Works
❌ Not recommended for production


---

✅ Permanent Fix Options

🔧 Option 1 — Regenerate Certificate (BEST)

You need to create new cert and update Quay.

Step 1: Generate new cert

openssl req -newkey rsa:4096 -nodes -sha256 \
-keyout quay.key \
-x509 -days 3650 \
-out quay.crt \
-subj "/CN=bastion-sno.lab.ocp.lan"


---

Step 2: Replace cert in Quay config

Your Quay config directory:

/root/quay-config

Place:

quay.crt
quay.key

Update config if needed.


---

Step 3: Restart Quay

podman restart quay-app


---

🔧 Option 2 — Trust existing cert (only if not expired)

❌ Not applicable here (already expired)


---

🔧 Option 3 — Always use insecure (NOT recommended)

In /etc/containers/registries.conf:

[[registry]]
location = "bastion-sno.lab.ocp.lan:8443"
insecure = true

👉 Works but insecure


---

🚀 Recommended for OCP Mirror Setup

👉 Use valid long-term cert (10 years)
👉 Or use internal CA and trust it


